7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
8 Section 1. Chapter 52 of Title 51 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950,
9 comprised of R.S. 51:3081 and 3082, is hereby enacted to read as follows:
10 CHAPTER 52. DEBIT CARD SURCHARGE
11 §3081. Debit card surcharge; prohibiting certain excess fees; liability;
12 definitions
13 A. As used in this Chapter:
14 (1) "Cardholder" means the person named on the face of a debit card to
15 whom or for whose benefit the debit card is issued by an issuer and includes any
16 employee or other agent or authorized user of the card.
17 (2) "Debit card" means a card or other payment device that debits funds
18 directly from a cardholder's deposit account.
19 (3) "Retail business" means any person or entity engaged in the sale of
20 goods or services.
21 (4) "Surcharge" means any additional amount of money imposed at the
22 time of the transaction by a retail business that increases the charge to the
23 cardholder for the privilege of using a debit card.
24 B. In a sale of goods or services, a retail business shall not impose a
25 surcharge on a cardholder who uses a debit card instead of cash, check, credit
26 card, or any other similar means of payment.
27 C.(1) A retail business that violates the provisions of this Section shall be
